OL,3,CSex cult leader could be moved to open
OL,4,Cprison under Parole Board
OL,5,Crecommendation
OL,7,FA spokesperson for the Parole Board
OL,8,Fsaid the panel "reflected on the
OL,9,Fgravity of the index offences and the
OL,10,Fprofound harm caused to victims."
OL,12,F"Mr Batley had shown a commitment in
OL,13,Fprison to address his risk to others
OL,14,Fand had completed all recommended
OL,15,Fwork," they said.
OL,17,F"After considering the progress made
OL,18,Fand the evidence presented at the
OL,19,Fhearing, the panel was not satisfied
OL,20,Fthat release at this point would be
OL,21,Fsafe for the protection of the public.
